1
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:19,720
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

2
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:36,799
Hello. Welcome to Top Gear,

3
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,519
where tonight we're mixing it up.

4
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:42,119
We're going to do the show
a little bit differently.

5
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:43,559
It's in 3D. Raargh!

6
00:00:43,560 --> 00:00:45,759
No, I'm only joking.
Fred, take it away.

7
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:48,239
Because we're not kicking off
with him skidding around

8
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,479
in a shiny supercar.

9
00:00:49,480 --> 00:00:52,639
Or trying to kill Fred
in new and inventive ways.

10
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:55,799
No, we're kicking off with
a question - what if?

11
00:00:55,800 --> 00:01:00,039
What if we could actually make a
genuine difference to a few lives,

12
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:01,359
give a bit back?

13
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:04,000
So we're kicking off with
a little experiment.

14
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:15,999
In the world of motorsports, life
at the top is fast, glamorous

15
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,920
and very exclusive.

16
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:23,719
No matter how talented you might be,
the simple truth is that,

17
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:27,479
without the right connections
and a whole heap of cash,

18
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:31,080
it's nigh on impossible to crack.

19
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,559
So here's the experiment.

20
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:41,479
What would happen if we developed
our very own race team,

21
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:44,239
a race team of young drivers and
mechanics,

22
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:48,039
who haven't got the connections
and who haven't got the cash,

23
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:51,120
and dropped them right in at the
deep end?

24
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:57,079
That deep end looks like this -

25
00:01:57,080 --> 00:02:01,639
contesting a round of the
prestigious GT Cup race series...

26
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,560
..at Donington Park.

27
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:11,079
800 hopefuls applied

28
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:14,279
and, from them, we selected 13
of the brightest young talents

29
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,840
in the UK...

30
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:20,400
..and set up a test day to see
what they were made of.

31
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:27,759
Today means a lot to me because it's
given me an opportunity

32
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,239
that I didn't think I'd ever have.

33
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:32,279
I'm meeting a lot of people,
learning a lot from other people.

34
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,559
I started racing when I was an
11-year-old.

35
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,040
I've been driving since I was three.

36
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:40,599
I'm here for a bit of mechanics
today, working on the MX-5 here,

37
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,800
do a bit of bolt and grease.

38
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:48,880
The Top Gear race team needs
two mechanics and two drivers.

39
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:53,079
So, to help choose them and then
train them up,

40
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:57,320
I called in professional
race team Paddock Motorsport.

41
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:02,199
Well, today we're looking for a
diamond in the rough, basically.

42
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:04,159
We're not looking
for a finished article.

43
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:06,919
We just want somebody who's
good at taking instruction

44
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,719
and is very mouldable.

45
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:12,399
These guys are going to come
in with experience from other

46
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:15,039
disciplines, so it's very important
that we can understand

47
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,880
how to take that forward.

48
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:20,720
Louis, take your time with the
gears, buddy. Don't rush it.

49
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:27,280
All right, mate. If you want to
crack into it. The tools are here.

50
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:32,399
A good mechanic needs a very good
attention to detail,

51
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,959
basically for fault-finding,

52
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:36,080
anything that's happened on the
circuit.

53
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,679
I love being a mechanic
because you spend so much time

54
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:43,360
and energy working on this one thing
to get that little bit faster.

55
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:48,679
The youngsters are a talented bunch,

56
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:53,199
one that knows all too well
that skill alone isn't enough

57
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,639
to get to the top.

58
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:57,199
I haven't got loads of money
just to chuck at a car.

59
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:59,359
I'd say money plays a big part in
it, yeah,

60
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:01,400
Money and opportunity, definitely.

61
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,319
With so much to play for,

62
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:09,040
Paddock Motorsport can only choose
those that show the most potential.

63
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:14,520
And, once the dust settles,
we have our four.

64
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:21,160
In the garage, mechanics Lillie
and Callum.

65
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:26,760
Out on track,
drivers Louis and Ollie.

66
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:35,240
With the race team assembled,
now it was time to train them.

67
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:40,279
Boot camp starts just a few days
later,

68
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:43,120
at Pembrey racetrack in
Carmarthenshire...

69
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:51,560
..where Louis is straight out on
track with driving coach Michael.

70
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,839
Open that up wider.

71
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,120
Good lad.

72
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:09,000
Not messing around, is he?
No, going for it.

73
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:14,799
Back in his hometown of Croydon,

74
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:19,399
our first young driver's racing
career has so far played out

75
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:22,080
at the local rental karting centre.

76
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:26,079
At the moment, I'm working at
Gatwick Airport as a ramp agent,

77
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:28,759
where we handle people's suitcases.

78
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:31,239
It's usually me saving up my weekly
pay

79
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,679
and just putting it aside for
go-karting.

80
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,799
Louis has the raw potential,

81
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:38,800
but this experiment
will be a big test.

82
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,519
When I got the phone call
saying I'm in the team,

83
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:46,039
I was just so over the moon.

84
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:48,160
Just got to make the most of it.

85
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:52,999
Mate, really good. Really good.
Good lad.

86
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,439
Feeling all right? Yeah, good.

87
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:57,720
Totally different to karting.

88
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:07,519
It might be new territory for Louis,
but the Paddock race engineers

89
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:11,279
reveal he's already had
a promising start.

90
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:14,119
Yeah. On your last lap there, Louis,

91
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:17,399
you were... You got yourself to
within five seconds of Martin.

92
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,079
Wow.

93
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:22,000
Can you just slow it down
a little bit, like, this...?!

94
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,559
It's a good start, guys.

95
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:32,999
In the garage, meanwhile, mechanics
Lillie and Callum

96
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,599
are already well
into their engineering crash course

97
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:39,760
on Paddock's second race-spec MX-5.

98
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:43,999
These coils commonly fail
due to the heat.

99
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,800
That's why after every session
we take them out.

100
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:51,399
Two kids coming in as apprentices
will not even get within touching

101
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:54,919
distance of a car on a team for the
first three or even four years.

102
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:56,799
So the guys out there driving,

103
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,519
you can actually be in a car
driving one quicker

104
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:02,399
than you can be a mechanic
out here in the pit lane.

105
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,719
Absolutely. I mean, the biggest
thing to remember

106
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,279
is the responsibility.

107
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:08,800
One mistake, one missed
bolt - it's someone's life.

108
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,799
That's totally shocked me,

109
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,239
the three or four-year thing.

110
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,960
I never realised that, myself.

111
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:20,079
Our young mechanics are definitely
in at the deep end

112
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:23,999
but Cornwall-based Lillie
and Lincolnshire lad Callum

113
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,639
have both grown up with that
mechanical mind-set

114
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:30,039
that might just help them swim.

115
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,240
Excellent stuff.

116
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:35,999
I like living in my lorry
because it's quiet.

117
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,799
No-one's around and I can do
whatever I want, really,

118
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:42,919
be in the shed on the cars
till whatever time.

119
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:46,319
Recently bought a couple
of bangers, got to strip them

120
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,519
and then build them
ready for racing.

121
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:50,599
First of all, before she'd done
the mechanics,

122
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,039
she used to do show jumping.

123
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:56,079
She came back from a show and said,
"I don't want to do this any more.

124
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,879
"I want to do bangers."

125
00:07:57,880 --> 00:08:00,639
Started at 11 doing banger racing.

126
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,599
Pretty much smash everyone else

127
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:05,279
up and hope you don't hurt yourself,
really!

128
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,679
Every time we'd blow up an engine,

129
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:09,719
me and my brother would change
engines together.

130
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:12,799
I love being a mechanic because
you find a problem, you fix it,

131
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:15,560
you get dirty and it's satisfying.

132
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:20,720
At 16, I started here as a HGV
mechanic apprentice.

133
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:24,279
Morning, Kev. Morning!

134
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:26,799
I worked in the garage
with my dad and his friend.

135
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:29,439
It was brilliant.
It's a good atmosphere.

136
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:32,559
After school, I went to college
and got an apprenticeship.

137
00:08:32,560 --> 00:08:34,880
I did two years in a
Land Rover garage.

138
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,239
It seems to come easy.

139
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:40,599
If you kind of think about it
logically, it all clicks together.

140
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,040
Just something I really enjoy.

141
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,159
Back out on track,

142
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:53,240
driver Ollie's training with Michael
is now also well under way.

143
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:56,320
Close the car in. Cross those arms.

144
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:59,959
And back home, in North Yorkshire,

145
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:05,479
this is a young man who spends every
spare minute in or around race cars.

146
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,559
I've never really been an academic
lad.

147
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:10,639
I'd much rather spend my evenings
in the garage with my dad,

148
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:12,040
tinkering with the cars.

149
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:20,439
Ollie, his dad, mum and brother
all compete on the dirt oval tracks

150
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:23,040
of National Autograss racing.

151
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:29,120
And, to help pay his way, Ollie
works full-time building generators.

152
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:32,399
The money that goes into the car
comes in your pocket

153
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,759
and goes out the next minute.

154
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:36,279
What else would you want
to spend your money on at 19?

155
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:39,080
Not many nights out are allowed, but
yeah, it's good.

156
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:42,039
There's lots of other sacrifices
as well.

157
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,599
It's like we don't do foreign
holidays.

158
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:49,239
Our holidays are spent in a camper
van, racing Saturday and Sunday,

159
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:50,919
back home and back to work

160
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:53,840
to earn some more pennies
to do it all again next week.

161
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,919
A former junior and open champion,

162
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:01,959
Ollie has plenty of race experience.

163
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,119
Down to quarter to three

164
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:05,759
and cross your arms,
if you need a bit more lock.

165
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:10,280
But the move from dirt to tarmac
is not to be underestimated.

166
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,519
What was he saying about feeding
the wheel?

167
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:15,519
Was that a habit from
grass-tracking?

168
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:18,279
Basically, because we only
go around an oval,

169
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:19,559
I don't cross my arms.

170
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:22,559
I've never crossed my arms because
that's quite slow in our sport.

171
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:24,959
The reason he's saying that is,
if you keep your hands there,

172
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:27,199
you know which way the steering
wheel is pointing. Yeah.

173
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,719
So, if ever you get out of shape,
you know, you just point

174
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:31,639
and that's kind of where you're
pointing.

175
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,120
To get you out of trouble. Yeah.

176
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:38,519
It's been an intensive first
day for the team,

177
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:41,519
but then, with the challenge
that lies ahead of them,

178
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:42,959
it needed to be.

179
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,279
Seven weeks' time,

180
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:46,799
they're going to be on track
with professional drivers. Yeah.

181
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:49,759
When you tell me things
like that and I think about it,

182
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:51,439
I get very anxious.

183
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:54,319
Seven weeks, seven weeks!

184
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,800
It's not a lot of time, is it?
It's a tall order.

185
00:10:57,920 --> 00:11:01,479
By doing something like this,
we're giving them a chance to sort

186
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:06,519
of fulfil their dreams,
but also to show their talents.

187
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:10,439
For me, personally, it's a real
passion project because it's nice

188
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,679
to be in a position to give
them that chance now

189
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:14,879
and to watch them grow.

190
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:20,800
The dream for me in doing the film
like this is someone notices them.

191
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:37,319
While the mechanics spend the next
week getting stuck in at Paddock HQ,

192
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:40,120
driver coaching steps up a gear.

193
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:45,439
Louis and Ollie have been studying
hard to get their race licences.

194
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,880
Your chariot awaits, sir.

195
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,959
And now, out on track,

196
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:54,560
it's their first ever go
on a live circuit in the MX-5.

197
00:12:01,880 --> 00:12:03,999
My only concern for them today
would be

198
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,760
if the nerves got the better of
them.

199
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,160
Fast cars coming
up and overtaking them...

200
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:12,959
OK. Stay on your line, buddy.
Stay on your line.

201
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:17,199
Michael takes each driver out
on track for tuition.

202
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:20,960
But, in busy traffic, mistakes are
made.

203
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:35,839
Get the line right, mate,
before we try and carry the speed.

204
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:37,679
You're trying to carry the
speed too soon.

205
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:39,360
Let it flow. Let it come to you.

206
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,639
All too soon,

207
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:45,680
the team will be back at Donington
for the GT Cup.

208
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:51,480
There's no choice but to dust
off and keep pushing forward.

209
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:58,959
Training reaches the halfway point

210
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:02,480
and the team are at
Cadwell Park in Lincolnshire.

211
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:07,759
The Paddock experts need to see
how they're shaping up

212
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:13,039
by giving them their first race
together in the Mazda SuperCup.

213
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:16,279
Cadwell couldn't be a more difficult
place to bring two newbies

214
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:19,080
for their first ever race weekend
in a car they're unfamiliar with.

215
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:24,559
It's tight, it's narrow,
it's undulating, it's unsighted.

216
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:27,199
Mazda weekends, you never know
what can get thrown at you,

217
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,880
so anything can happen.

218
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:34,800
The team has been practising
at Cadwell for a couple of days.

219
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:41,239
And the challenging circuit hasn't
just been a test for the drivers.

220
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:44,679
First practice, he broke his
gearbox,

221
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:47,080
so came back in and changed that.

222
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:50,879
He went out again and then went
in the wall

223
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:53,640
and bent his steering rack,
so we had to change that.

224
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:57,919
Gearbox weren't too bad. The
steering rack's just fiddly.

225
00:13:57,920 --> 00:13:59,599
Cos the radiator's in the way.

226
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:01,439
all the belts and everything.

227
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:03,959
Don't break the car.
We haven't got any more.

228
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:05,520
Yeah, try not to.

229
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:15,119
But, as the more relaxed practice
sessions end, the mood shifts.

230
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:20,240
The focus is now on the team's
first ever competitive race.

231
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:25,679
It ain't right. Oh, BLEEP this
all. No need, is there?

232
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:27,399
All right, buddy, you ready? Yeah.

233
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:29,480
Forget about yesterday. Yeah.

234
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:33,319
Focus on today, all right? All
right.

235
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:35,599
You'll be fine. Good luck.

236
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,160
All the best. Thank you.

237
00:14:39,280 --> 00:14:45,320
Louis and Ollie join a 27-car grid,
one that's split into two classes.

238
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:51,039
Pros starting towards the front
and the amateur club class

239
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,759
that the boys have qualified
in the middle of

240
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:55,680
