00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:08,319
by a full analysis of the drive with
the Paddock coaching team.

299
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:10,879
I think where you were getting
a little bit frustrated,

300
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,639
where you had your bit of a moment,

301
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:15,719
I think there, was just trying
to go just too deep.

302
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:17,879
Going through the data
has been amazing.

303
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:20,879
Giving me them tips,
just where I can find

304
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:24,719
that last few tenth of a second to
improve my overall lap.

305
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:26,879
I know what to do for my
races tomorrow.

306
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:29,840
So, hopefully, I have no
problems and it'll be a good race.

307
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:37,479
With the two races left to run that
weekend, the next morning,

308
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:42,240
Louis and Ollie set out to put
the theory into practice.

309
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:49,359
There goes Oliver Hall up
the inside, that was a late move.

310
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:51,959
Can he hold the inside line?

311
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:55,119
He's later on the brakes and
he will slip through.

312
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:57,559
Proving a very spectacular driver
to watch, is Oliver.

313
00:18:57,560 --> 00:18:59,919
The first race gets under way well,

314
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:03,239
with Ollie maintaining his
impressive form.

315
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,600
Oliver Hall,
very quick reactions there.

316
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:11,560
As the race progresses, though,
the real star student is Louis.

317
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:16,759
And Louis Smithen has got himself
ahead of Oliver Hall, look.

318
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:19,480
Really coming on strong in the
second half of the race.

319
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:25,839
After a hard-fought
battle to the line...

320
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:27,039
Oh, big contact!

321
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:29,399
And that's Oliver Hall involved.

322
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:31,960
..Ollie hangs on to finish
fourth in class.

323
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:39,799
And with Louis a place ahead of him,
Team Top Gear has its first podium.

324
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:44,199
Well done, Louis. Come on, lad.
Get in there! Well done. Thank you.

325
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,959
Good stuff.

326
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:48,639
It's a huge boost for the team.

327
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:50,920
And Louis isn't done yet.

328
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:55,199
The lights go out,
we're away and racing.

329
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:59,599
In the last battle of the weekend,
a mistake from Ollie sees him

