00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,600
playing catch-up from the off.

331
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:07,040
But Louis is in the zone.

332
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:10,079
Turning all that data,

333
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:15,279
the analysis and the coaching
into a clean race to the finish.

334
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:18,760
A really impressive end
to his MX-5 SuperCup debut.

335
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:23,399
The second podium of the weekend,
Louis Smithen!

336
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:26,600
It's an incredible
result for the Croydon karter.

337
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,919
While, for team-mate Ollie,
Cadwell has given him

338
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:35,319
another important lesson
about the roller-coaster of racing.

339
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:37,439
Yeah, I'm devastated.

