00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:41,319
Let the pressure get to me, maybe.

342
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:42,599
For the whole team,

343
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:47,240
this first race meeting has been
a massive step forward.

344
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:58,079
To keep the momentum going, a few
days later, I organise an outing.

345
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:01,719
The aim is to give the team
the inspiration they'll need to

346
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:04,200
push on as the stakes get higher.

347
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:11,199
The place is the home
of the McLaren Formula 1 team.

348
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:13,639
Is that Senna's car? Yeah.

349
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:17,640
This is one of the most successful
cars in race history.

350
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:20,799
For more than six decades,

351
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:23,680
McLaren has been
a leader in world motorsport.

352
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:28,519
James Hunt, Niki Lauda,
Senna, Hamilton,

353
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:31,199
all raced and won with McLaren.

354
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:34,519
If you want to be the best, you've
got to learn from

355
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:38,719
the absolute best, so I've got a
special guest for you to meet today.

356
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:44,239
Current McLaren F1 driver and
all-round superstar,

357
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:45,799
Lando Norris.

358
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:48,399
Oh, my gosh. Here he is!

359
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,759
Good morning.

360
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:51,559
We've got Callum, Lando.
Nice to meet you.

361
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,679
Lillie. Good to meet you, hello.
Hello. How are you?

362
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:56,159
Ollie. Nice to meet you, mate.
And Louis. All right?

363
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:57,599
They're our drivers.

364
00:21:57,600 --> 00:22:00,279
These two keep the team alive,
these are the mechanics.

