525
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:15,239
isn't that right, Christopher?
It is, Patrick.

526
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:17,519
And the hot hatch we need to talk
about is this one -

527
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:19,639
the Honda Civic Type R,

528
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:23,359
which, for a long time, has been
the most in-your-face hot hatch

529
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:27,319
of the lot, getting fightier and
angrier generation on generation.

530
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:31,480
And now, buckle up, because
there's a new one on the scene.

531
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:38,479
Well, here's a turn-up
for the books.

532
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:41,039
This is the new Honda Civic Type R

533
00:31:41,040 --> 00:31:42,879
and in a break with tradition,

534
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:48,360
it doesn't look like it should be
wearing an ankle tag. In fact...

535
00:31:49,880 --> 00:31:52,719
..the world's most thuggish
hot hatch

536
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:56,280
looks like it's gone a bit grown-up.

537
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:58,799
But fear not,

538
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:04,319
because under that sensible new
suit, the Civic Type R is still...

539
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:05,399
ENGINE REVS

540
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:08,160
TYRES SQUEAL

541
00:32:09,240 --> 00:32:12,760
..an absolute delinquent!

542
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:20,159
It's got more power
than ever before.

543
00:32:20,160 --> 00:32:25,679
324 horsepower from a two-litre
turbo-charged engine.

544
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:28,639
OK, that's only a few more
horsepower than the old one,

545
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:32,639
but it'll still do 170mph.

546
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:34,880
0-60 in five seconds.

547
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:37,719
I mean, how much more do you want?

548
00:32:37,720 --> 00:32:40,440
That's immense
for a little hot hatchback.

549
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:45,279
And while more and more fast
hatchbacks are turning up

550
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:48,239
with sensible four-wheel drive
these days,

551
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:51,520
the Civic remains
defiantly old school.

552
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:56,559
Hot Hatches should, in my book,
be front wheel drive.

553
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:59,399
That's the whole point of them.

554
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:02,439
What's the upside?
Weight is the upside.

555
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:06,119
Probably 200kg less than
a four-wheel-drive equivalent.

556
00:33:06,120 --> 00:33:08,119
TYRES SQUEAL

557
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:11,559
Look at this.
It's got a proper manual gearbox.

558
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:14,599
Third, second.

559
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:17,759
Honda are masters
at these manual shifts.

560
00:33:17,760 --> 00:33:20,639
Describe this new one...

561
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:24,279
It is exceptionally rigid,
yet smooth,

562
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:27,320
and that is not remotely amusing.

563
00:33:28,480 --> 00:33:32,199
And this car reminds us what a hot
hatch should be like inside.

564
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:37,159
It's basic. Not too much going on,
but the seat is just exquisite.

565
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:40,359
I think it's the best seat
I've ever sat, in a fast car.

566
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:43,719
I've got dials everywhere.
I've got Honda quality.

567
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:47,439
But it's not trying to be grown-up.
It's not trying to be a luxury car.

568
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:51,040
It shouts -
"Get in me and thrash me!"

569
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:54,840
Which isn't remotely amusing,
either.

570
00:33:56,640 --> 00:34:00,839
What is amusing is just how much
work Honda has put in

571
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:04,199
to the bits
that no-one will ever notice.

572
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:06,639
They're very proud
of the turbocharger,

573
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:09,679
which is 3% more efficient.

574
00:34:09,680 --> 00:34:12,319
Now, that might not sound like much
to you and I,

575
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:17,720
but to some Honda engineer,
that was four years of hard work.

576
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:22,439
Exhaust flow improved 13%.

577
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:25,519
Torsional rigidity improved 15%.

578
00:34:25,520 --> 00:34:29,159
These are all tiny improvements,
but lumped together,

579
00:34:29,160 --> 00:34:30,719
they result in a driving experience

580
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:35,159
that's just brighter and sharper
than ever before.

581
00:34:35,160 --> 00:34:36,799
Just feels so alive.

582
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:38,720
A car that makes you smile.

583
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:43,199
Ha-ha-ha!

584
00:34:43,200 --> 00:34:47,200
This reminds me
of being young and stupid.

585
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:51,799
In fact, there's only
one real issue here,

586
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:53,999
and it's not with the car.

587
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:58,199
Hot hatches are not designed
for big, open airfields.

588
00:34:58,200 --> 00:35:01,479
They're about cross-country
point-to-point pace.

589
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:03,760
They're about B-roads.

590
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:10,919
But the trouble with B-roads is that
they come with real world problems

591
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:15,839
like speed limits and speed cameras
and other traffic.

592
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:18,120
Well, not any more.

593
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:23,959
Introducing the B-Road-a-Matic 3000

594
00:35:23,960 --> 00:35:28,759
for when you simply must add
interest to your desolate airfield.

595
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:32,039
I know it may look like a tractor
with a couple of pots of paint

596
00:35:32,040 --> 00:35:33,359
strapped to the back

597
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:35,599
but it's actually a very technical
piece of equipment

598
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,839
developed over many, many months,

599
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:40,120
and I'm extremely proud of it.

600
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:45,479
And with my very own B-road
now open for business,

601
00:35:45,480 --> 00:35:50,680
