I mean, how the hell in the '80s,
did we fit in them?

718
00:43:14,280 --> 00:43:17,599
Cos in the '80s, Paddy, we were
kids. We were smaller.

719
00:43:17,600 --> 00:43:21,399
You were never that small. You're
like Donkey Kong in Mario Kart.

720
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:23,759
You driving around in one
of them is unbelievable.

721
00:43:23,760 --> 00:43:28,399
So go on, then, Pad, fresh pair
of eyes on it, which one you having?

722
00:43:28,400 --> 00:43:30,199
It's a tricky one because

723
00:43:30,200 --> 00:43:33,559
17-year-old Pad would
have loved one of them. I get that.

724
00:43:33,560 --> 00:43:37,959
On the other hand, 17-year-old Pad
would have loved one of them.

725
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:40,599
Similar prices?
Well, same ballpark.

726
00:43:40,600 --> 00:43:43,479
Oh, it's a tricky one.
They're both so good.

727
00:43:43,480 --> 00:43:45,359
I'm going to have to
go for the Civic. Yeah.

728
00:43:45,360 --> 00:43:47,039
I'm going to have to go
for the Civic

729
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:50,799
but I'd pop the Peugeot in the boot
for a blast down memory lane

730
00:43:50,800 --> 00:43:53,719
every now and again.
Perfect two-car garage.

731
00:43:53,720 --> 00:43:57,799
Right, that's that sorted. Now we
must get back to our young race team

732
00:43:57,800 --> 00:44:01,240
where things
were about to get really serious.

733
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:08,359
Just seven weeks since our young
team first came together,

734
00:44:08,360 --> 00:44:12,680
this bold experiment
is reaching its conclusion.

735
00:44:14,080 --> 00:44:17,199
A band of talented drivers
and mechanics

736
00:44:17,200 --> 00:44:21,720
whose racing ambitions
could never have reached so far...

737
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:27,039
..are now going wheel-to-wheel
with a multimillion pound grid

738
00:44:27,040 --> 00:44:30,519
of hardened racers in the GT Cup.

739
00:44:30,520 --> 00:44:33,999
It's extremely tough. They really
have to soak up everything

740
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:38,759
that we say like a sponge, not get
overwhelmed by the whole experience.

741
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:40,599
From what we've seen of them
in the car so far,

742
00:44:40,600 --> 00:44:42,599
you know, they're adapting to it
very, very well

743
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:44,360
and taking it on board very quickly.

744
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:47,999
It's pre-race practice.

745
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:52,399
Louis and Ollie have had two weeks
intensive training with the car

746
00:44:52,400 --> 00:44:54,759
and now it's their last chance
to prepare.

747
00:44:54,760 --> 00:44:57,359
We've got brand-new brakes
on the front...

748
00:44:57,360 --> 00:45:02,159
30% brake pressure, 50%, 70.

749
00:45:02,160 --> 00:45:04,759
The warm-up session doesn't
just give them the chance

750
00:45:04,760 --> 00:45:06,999
to set the car up for the track,

751
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:10,399
it's also the driver's
one opportunity

752
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:13,199
to rehearse crucial moments
of the race to come.

753
00:45:13,200 --> 00:45:15,119
I want you to practise
the driver chain

754
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:17,519
as they come into the pits hot.

755
00:45:17,520 --> 00:45:20,999
Hit your marks on the board. Get out
the car as quick as can, Louis,

756
00:45:21,000 --> 00:45:23,759
then you're jumping in,
waiting for the push back.

757
00:45:23,760 --> 00:45:25,919
Remember, once the lollipop
releases you,

758
00:45:25,920 --> 00:45:27,359
you've got to mash that throttle.

759
00:45:27,360 --> 00:45:30,760
Full faith on him. You just got to
go into the fast lane and go.

760
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:36,119
For mechanics Lillie and Callum,
meanwhile,

761
00:45:36,120 --> 00:45:39,679
working with the McLaren
has meant finding their place

762
00:45:39,680 --> 00:45:42,599
in a professional pit crew.
Lillie and Callum have gelled well

763
00:45:42,600 --> 00:45:44,519
with their team.
They get on with everybody.

764
00:45:44,520 --> 00:45:47,319
They've stepped up to the next
level, checking suspension,

765
00:45:47,320 --> 00:45:49,479
you know, we changed brakes
yesterday

766
00:45:49,480 --> 00:45:51,240
and I think they'll do
really well today.

767
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:55,119
The whole team
has raised their game.

768
00:45:55,120 --> 00:45:57,719
But as practice comes to an end,

769
00:45:57,720 --> 00:46:01,879
the real test starts now.

770
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:03,880
Just, uh...

771
00:46:05,800 --> 00:46:08,399
..keeping everything crossed.

772
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:10,359
We've got 20 minutes
and then we're out.

773
00:46:10,360 --> 00:46:13,079
So the call for the tyres will be
a little bit earlier. Yeah. Yeah.

774
00:46:13,080 --> 00:46:15,919
So I want you guys out. You got
gloves? I'll get some now. Yeah.

775
00:46:15,920 --> 00:46:19,719
You want good ones. Yeah? Cos the
pull for the tyres will strain you.

776
00:46:19,720 --> 00:46:21,399
All right. Yeah. Yeah?

777
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:23,560
You good? Yeah. Thank you.

778
00:46:25,000 --> 00:46:28,799
The incredible field that makes up
the GT Cup grid

779
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:32,759
is divided into six
competitive categories.

780
00:46:32,760 --> 00:46:37,319
Team Top Gear is competing
in the GTH class

781
00:46:37,320 --> 00:46:42,000
against nine other McLarens,
Porsches and AMG Mercs.

782
00:46:43,760 --> 00:46:45,799
As a team endurance event,

783
00:46:45,800 --> 00:46:49,319
both drivers will have to
prove themselves.

784
00:46:49,320 --> 00:46:52,360
First with the qualifying rounds.

785
00:46:56,040 --> 00:46:57,839
On new tyres, low fuel,

786
00:46:57,840 --> 00:47:00,560
he's going to get about three laps
to do a time.

787
00:47:03,520 --> 00:47:05,399
My boy.

788
00:47:05,400 --> 00:47:08,679
Yeah, he's my
little gentle giant.

789
00:47:08,680 --> 00:47:12,999
I know he's in a really,
really fast car.

790
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:15,720
Yeah, my heart should be
palpitating.

791
00:47:16,920 --> 00:47:20,120
But I've got confidence in him
and he's a confident lad as well.

792
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:26,199
Do you believe how mad it is
from karting to doing this?

793
00:47:26,200 --> 00:47:28,279
I mean, it's mad, isn't it?
It is crazy.

794
00:47:28,280 --> 00:47:31,760
Oh, I'm buzzing for you.
Buzzing for you.

795
00:47:38,800 --> 00:47:42,719
I can't believe that my boy

796
00:47:42,720 --> 00:47:44,799
is competing at this level.

797
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:47,080
I just couldn't be more proud.

798
00:47:48,480 --> 00:47:51,559
The opportunity which he's had here
is something that's unobtainable

799
00:47:51,560 --> 00:47:55,079
to the working man.
You can't afford to race a McLaren.

800
00:47:55,080 --> 00:47:57,400
You can't afford to sit
in a McLaren.

801
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:04,199
Louis and Ollie's first-ever
competitive performance in the car

802
00:48:04,200 --> 00:48:09,079
is enough to qualify them
8th in class.

803
00:48:09,080 --> 00:48:12,399
And now the end of the road
for Team Top Gear

804
00:48:12,400 --> 00:48:19,000
lies on the other side of
a 50-minute endurance race.

805
00:48:20,480 --> 00:48:23,839
A race where each driver
gets a stint,

806
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:28,159
swapping midway
with a full team pit stop.

807
00:48:28,160 --> 00:48:31,319
Competing right through to the
chequered flag would need them

808
00:48:31,320 --> 00:48:34,040
ALL to be on their game.

809
00:48:35,320 --> 00:48:37,599
Right, guys,
it's time to get serious now.

810
00:48:37,600 --> 00:48:40,839
This whole journey is pointed
to the GT Cup race.

811
00:48:40,840 --> 00:48:43,399
50-minute race.
I want Louis to start

812
00:48:43,400 --> 00:48:46,359
and then for you, Ollie, to bring
home the chequered flag. Perfect.

813
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:48,440
Come on, lads. Let's do it.

814
00:49:04,800 --> 00:49:06,839
I'm more nervous
watching this than...

815
00:49:06,840 --> 00:49:08,279
I know, it's the thing, isn't it?

816
00:49:08,280 --> 00:49:11,319
You just want them to be safe,
don't you? They're like your kids.

817
00:49:11,320 --> 00:49:14,559
Our stomachs are in knots. Imagine
what their bloody dads are like.

818
00:49:14,560 --> 00:49:18,399
Louis is approaching the end
of the formation lap,

819
00:49:18,400 --> 00:49:22,479
and the rolling start
is just seconds away.

820
00:49:22,480 --> 00:49:25,559
It's time to find out
how this team reacts

821
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:27,999
when he comes to the big moment.

822
00:49:28,000 --> 00:49:30,840
Lights are on on the gantry.
They go out now.

823
00:49:32,080 --> 00:49:35,159
And we get Round 20 of the 2022
Championship season under way

824
00:49:35,160 --> 00:49:36,480
for GT Cup.

825
00:49:39,280 --> 00:49:41,439
Come on! Come on, Louis!

826
00:49:41,440 --> 00:49:45,160
It looks as though everybody
is safely through the first corner.

827
00:49:51,680 --> 00:49:53,439
Louis came on the radio and says,

828
00:49:53,440 --> 00:49:55,680
"The car in front
is slowing me down."

829
00:49:58,920 --> 00:50:00,919
It takes a bit of skill,
a bit of experience.

830
00:50:00,920 --> 00:50:03,399
So you've got to work out
where you are quicker during the lap

831
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:05,160
and then pick your moment.

832
00:50:13,840 --> 00:50:15,600
Has he got him? Yeah, got him.

833
00:50:17,320 --> 00:50:20,679
Pace is really good.
Faster than that car in front.

834
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:23,000
That car is running top three
in the points.

835
00:50:27,840 --> 00:50:31,440
Louis is making his mark
as he claws away at the field.

836
00:50:34,200 --> 00:50:36,199
All the while in the garage,

837
00:50:36,200 --> 00:50:39,319
the team's pit stop strategy
is being calculated.

838
00:50:39,320 --> 00:50:43,839
If he's got a bit of traffic,
we might get Ollie in to try

839
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:47,079
and do an undercut to try
and overtake during the pit stops.

840
00:50:47,080 --> 00:50:49,839
Or if Louis is in clean air,
just keep him out there.

841
00:50:49,840 --> 00:50:52,279
Just keep going.

842
00:50:52,280 --> 00:50:54,399
Get yourself ready, warmed up.

843
00:50:54,400 --> 00:50:56,600
Do something to me as well.

844
00:51:00,520 --> 00:51:04,119
Out on track, the battles
and drama continue...

845
00:51:04,120 --> 00:51:06,919
Whoa! Uh-oh! Oh!

846
00:51:06,920 --> 00:51:09,239
..but Louis is holding his own.

847
00:51:09,240 --> 00:51:11,159
There he is, there he is.

848
00:51:11,160 --> 00:51:13,200
Go on, go on, go on, go on.

849
00:51:16,520 --> 00:51:19,439
What do you think about his position
at the minute? You happy?

850
00:51:19,440 --> 00:51:21,159
Yeah, he's doing a good job.

851
00:51:21,160 --> 00:51:23,240
We're holding P7 right now.

852
00:51:31,480 --> 00:51:34,599
So this is number 25 car...
Go on, Louis!

853
00:51:34,600 --> 00:51:37,999
..going well in the hands of
Louis Smithen making his debut

854
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:41,920
in the Championship, scheduled
to hand the car over to Ollie Hall.

855
00:51:56,800 --> 00:51:59,359
The pit stop window opens

856
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:02,559
and the team in the garage
get ready to go to work.

857
00:52:02,560 --> 00:52:05,640
How long till he's in?
Three minutes.

858
00:52:08,080 --> 00:52:11,680
Whatever happens, happens. Do your
best, that's all we can ask for.

859
00:52:15,480 --> 00:52:16,680
Oh!

860
00:52:17,800 --> 00:52:19,120
Go on, Ol.

861
00:52:22,200 --> 00:52:24,080
Please confirm...

862
00:52:28,680 --> 00:52:30,040
Let's do it.

